ara]], French singer-songwriter and violinist * 1945 &ndash; [[Tammi Terrell]], American soul singer-songwriter (d. 1970) *[[1946]] &ndash; [[Aleksander Wolszczan]], Polish astronomer *[[1947]] &ndash; [[Serge Bernier]], Canadian ice hockey player * 1947 &ndash; [[Tommy James]], American singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer * 1947 &ndash; [[Johnny Miller]], American golfer and sportscaster * 1947 &ndash; [[Jim Ryun]], American runner and politician *[[1948]] &ndash; [[Bruce Cutler]], American lawyer *[[1950]] &ndash; [[Paul Holmes (broadcaster)|Paul Holmes]], New Zealand journalist (d. 2013) * 1950 &ndash; [[Phillip Noyce]], Australian director and producer * 1950 &ndash; [[Debbie Stabenow]], American social worker and politician *[[1951]] &ndash; [[Rick Burleson]], American baseball player * 1951 &ndash; [[Dale Earnhardt]], American race car driver (d. 2001) * 1951 &ndash; [[John Holmes (British diplomat)|John Holmes]], English diplomat, [[List of ambassadors of the United Kingdom to France|British Ambassador to France]] *[[1952]] &ndash; [[Nora Dunn]], American actress and comedian * 1952 &ndash; [[David Icke]], English footballer and sportscaster * 1952 &ndash; [[Bob McClure]], American baseball player and coach * 1952 &ndash; [[Rob Nicholson]], Canadian lawyer and politician, 11th [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Canada)|Canadian Minister of Foreign Affairs]] * 1952 &ndash; [[Ron Washington]], American baseball player and manager *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Jake Burton Carpenter]], American snowboarder and businessman, founded [[Burton Snowboards]] * 1954 &ndash; [[Jerry Seinfeld]], American comedian, actor, and producer *[[1955]] &ndash; [[Don McKinnon (rugby league)|Don McKinnon]], Australian rugby league player * 1955 &ndash; [[Kate Mulgrew]], American actress *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Karen Barad]], American physicist and philosopher *[[1957]] &ndash; [[Daniel Day-Lewis]], British-Irish actor <!-- dual citizen --> * 1957 &ndash; [[Mark Kendall (guitarist)|Mark Kendall