{{Infobox animanga/Header | name = Pro Wrestling Superstar Biography | image = Retsuden.jpg | caption = ''Pro Wrestling Superstar Retsuden'' volume 7 | ja_kanji = プロレススーパースター列伝 | ja_romaji = Pro Wrestling Superstar Retsuden | genre = <!-- Genres should be based on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. --> }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | author = [[Ikki Kajiwara]] | illustrator = Kunichika Harada | publisher = [[Shogakukan]] | demographic = ''[[Shōnen manga|Shōnen]]'' | magazine = [[Weekly Shōnen Sunday]] | first = 1980 | last = 1983 | volumes = 17 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
{{nihongo|'''''Pro Wrestling Superstar Biography'''''|プロレススーパースター列伝|Pro Wrestling Superstar Retsuden}} is a [[shōnen]] [[manga]] written by [[Ikki Kajiwara]] and drawn by Kunichika Harada. The manga was serialized in ''[[Weekly Shōnen Sunday]]'' from 1980 volume 23 through 1983 volume 26.<ref>{{cite web |title=週刊少年サンデー プロレススーパースター列伝(原田久仁信 ／ 梶原一騎 ／ [協力]アントニオ猪木) |url=https://mediaarts-db.bunka.go.jp/mg/magazine_works/6165 |website=Media Arts Database |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=November 10, 2018 |language=Japanese}}</ref>
==Plot== The manga is billed as a series of [[biographical]] stories, though elements were added for dramatic effect. The wrestlers profiled in the series were popular in Japan at the time of the manga's serialization.
